Bovine tuberculosis, Israel
---------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 8 Feb 2019 from Dr. Tamir Goshen, Acting Director, Veterinary Services and Animal Health, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, Beit Dagan, Israel

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 5 Feb 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 5 Feb 2019
Report date: 8 Feb 2019
Date submitted to OIE: 8 Feb 2019
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: September 1999
Manifestation of disease: Subclinical infection
Causal agent: _Mycobacterium caprae_
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic and advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (Devora): Devora, Yizreel, Hazafon
Date of start of the outbreak: 5 Feb 2019
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 254 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: A group of 254 imported calves were received at the farm on [3 Sep 2018]. The calves were born at the end of 2017 or the beginning of 2018. On [24 Dec 2018], the calf was slaughtered with 10 additional calves from the same group. In the slaughterhouse, lung lesions were seen in one calf and sent to the laboratory. No lesions were found in the other calves of this group, which were slaughtered on the same day or on other dates.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0.39 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Introduction of new live animals, legal movement of animals.
Epidemiological comments: The calf is an imported calf that was suspected of the disease at the slaughterhouse. Control measures that are taken are quarantine of the remaining calves of the group, tracking contacts and surveillance at the slaughterhouse. People who were in contact with the affected calf have been referred to the Ministry of Health.

Control measures
Measures applied: Traceability, quarantine, surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Abu Kabir TB Laboratory, Ministry of Health (national laboratory) / Cattle / Polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 5 Feb 2019 / Positive
Kimron Veterinary Institute, Bacteriology Department (national laboratory) / Cattle / Microscopic examination / 26 Dec 2018 / Inconclusive
Kimron Veterinary Institute, Bacteriology Department (national laboratory) / Cattle / Polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 5 Jan 2019 / Inconclusive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.]

